Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of Approximate Message Passing (AMP) algorithm for solving high-dimensional linear regression tasks with noisy, linear measurements. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of AMP in image/video-processing applications, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Markov random field prior distribution, which falls under statistical inference (cs.SI).
